<br>
I've never ever been a fan of root-rotting - unless I had to.  In those cases I'd often Heal ole Jober to keep him tanking.  Of course there are many places where Fear kiting won't work, due to adds.  In those cases a combo of tactics sometimes helps.<br>
<br>
A good example is soloing seafuries in OoT.  It's simply impossible to fear kite on that island without getting adds.  And the only thing worse than one of them hitting you HARD, is TWO of them hitting you HARDER!  This is where agro kiting comes in.  <br>
<br>
To use the seafuries as the example, you pull to the edge of the water and engage pet.  Lay on a dot.  Very often this agros the cyclops on you and you have to BACK UP BACK UP BACK UP down the beach to keep yourself alive.  This, of course also keeps the pet alive.  Soon enough the dot and pet have done their job and you can med and get ready for the next pull.  Sometimes in order to keep pet alive you have to SIT -- which is a taunt unto itself.  Run down the beach and when the he turns on the pet again, sit down again, etc.  To the clops, you are FAR more interesting than Jober.<br>
<br>
Lich series?  Always always.  Unless I've got KEI (which I ain't paying for!) I'm using the lich spells.  To not use Lich or the pet, you're not taking advantage of the wonderful powers of the class.  At later levels you get your Tap dots.  This allows you to have Lich on, cast the tap/dot and sit down... you're gaining health and mana at the same time.<br>
<br>
One other thing... I'd advise you to interrupt your solo adventures with regular grouping.  Not only does it keep you up on your skills, it reminds people (at least for an hour or so!) that necros are a valuable part of a group.  <br>
<br>
Also, it's good necro etiquette to NOT cast Fear when in a group unless they ask you to.  It's my belief that other classes (unconsciously) find it demeaning, unless the group lacks a healer (in which case you're the HERO!).  Garomtel used to complain all the time about grouping with necros because he'd go to all that trouble to PULL the mob, only to have to chase it when he got to camp.   <p>Sytox 58 Defiler<br>
