<br>
Screaming terror affects all mobs, not just undead. Well, unless they are highly resistant.<br>
<br>
I will add one tactic that was not covered. I found it very useful when going thru my exp grind. One bad thing, KEI is a must for this tactic. I will admit I was KEI'ed almost all of the time while grinding, but hey, thats what its there for.<br>
<br>
I will discuss quad kiting. Yup, look out tree huggers, we can do it to, only slightly varied. I found out this tactic by accident due to adds, but it can work if properly done.<br>
<br>
I pulled one mob with Dooming Darkness, send pet, fear. Then, o boy, another mob is coming. Since I know they are friendly aggro, guess what? Yup, its gonna jump my pet soon. Sooo, I dark it as well. Whats nice about it is that when you dark the potential add, it now hates you, so it ignores the pet now and comes at ya. Heres the tricky part, stay close to your pet and run around a bit till you can cast a DOT, hit the add with the DOT then root it. Dont fear it. Why? if you fear it and pet is not on it I found it will go the opposite way of the one your pet is back hitting. Not good to have two mobs going different directions. Then move inbetween your pet and the rooted mob. Re-fear the original as needed. soon your pet will lay waste to the original and now what? Wait for that root to break then fear the add, sick pet, rinse, repeat. (Any adds that come follow the plans for first add, dark, dot, root)<br>
<br>
I can tell you in EW I have had up to 5 Ice Giant Savages being eaten away by my DOTs. Yes it is very risky if you arent aware of your surroundings and what has friendly aggro.<br>
<br>
TIP 1 - When casting spin around to scan for adds or your next escape route. Dont worry about looking at the mob coming at you, if he is close enough to interrupt, he will do it regardless of whether your spinning or not.<br>
<br>
TIP 2 - If by chance the adds manages to hit you while the pet is on the original mob, he will attack it when he kills number one. Thats a bad thing unless you have the 49 pet. A pet on a rooted mob is not a good thing. So if you do get hit, make sure to /pet back off after he kills the first one.<br>
<br>
TIP 3 - Never stay seated for too long, especially in EW, griffons are fast and can come up behind you without warning. They hit for 100+ and just about interrupt everything. So, I suggest having harmshield up just in case you need it.<br>
<br>
So, in summary, if you are wanting to grind some exp, and can afford to get KEI to do it, make them tree huggers wimper by quading )<br>
