<br>
The first hp's to mana spell is Dark Pact, at level 8.  Allure of Death is the level 20 upgrade.  These spells work more efficiently than the equivalent level of breeze or clarity.  It's also why Necros are in skelly form all the time (some actually think we do this for a &quot;gee whiz&quot; effect).  <br>
<br>
The first tap over time is Leach, at level 12.  Check Casters Realm for the upgrade.  When I was level 20-40, I didn't use the dot tap much, I just tapped, which is a very nice &quot;nuke&quot;.  This results in mana and health that see-saw back and forth.  It's a great system unless you get into a tough battle and suddenly find you're low on both.  Without much mana, you can't/won't want to lifetap, and without much health, you can't afford to change it into mana.<br>
<br>
Then you just have to sit and rest like everyone else.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START  >D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/grin.gif ALT=" >D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
As far as I know, Feign Death has no specifics, it's just a die roll.  There may be a Dexterity connection.  Or maybe the better your Abjuration or something, the more likely you are to succeed at it.  I have it perma memmed and usually have good luck with it (I've been sole survivor of a total wipeout on a couple GCP raids).  Athame said he also found it useless, so you're not alone on this.  <br>
<br>
BTW. Harmshield is another great level 20 spell that you might try memming for a while.  Around 20-30 our spells start to steal agro from the tanks, and this little baby has a fast cast time.  While the mob is wailing on you and doing no damage, the tanks have time to taunt the nasty back to them. <p>Sytox 58 Defiler<br>
<br>
